configFile.desc:
Create config.json in the project root. Key settings:

{
  "server": {
    "port": 8080,
    "host": "0.0.0.0",
    "cors_origins": ["http://localhost:3000"]
  },
  "logging": { "level": "info", "format": "json" },
  "hitl": {
    "enabled": true,
    "input_timeout": "5m",
    "websocket_enabled": true
  },
  "agent": {
    "timeout": "30m"
  }
}

Specify at startup with --config config.json.

extensionsPlugins.detail:
## Plugin System

Enable plugins in the config file:

```json
{
  "plugin": {
    "enabled": true,
    "dir": ".claw/plugins"
  }
}
```

Plugins communicate via JSON-RPC protocol. The system auto-discovers and loads executables in the directory.

## MCP Servers

Configure external MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers:

```json
{
  "mcp": {
    "timeout": "30s",
    "servers": {
      "my-server": {
        "transport": "stdio",
        "command": "npx",
        "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem"]
      },
      "remote-server": {
        "transport": "sse",
        "url": "https://mcp.example.com/sse",
        "headers": { "Authorization": "Bearer token" }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Three transport methods supported:

| Transport | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| `stdio` | Local process, communicates via stdin/stdout |
| `sse` | Server-Sent Events, suitable for remote services |
| `http` | HTTP Streamable, recommended for new MCP |

## Custom Commands

Define shortcut commands in config.json:

```json
{
  "commands": {
    "review": {
      "description": "Code review",
      "template": "Please review the code quality of: {{args}}",
      "agent": "codereview"
    },
    "explain": {
      "description": "Code explanation",
      "template": "Please explain this code: {{args}}",
      "model": "gpt-3.5-turbo"
    }
  }
}
```

Usage: Type `/review main.go` or `/explain auth.go` in the CLI.

channelConfig.detail:
## DingTalk Configuration

```json
{
  "channel": {
    "dingtalk": {
      "enabled": true,
      "app_key": "your-app-key",
      "app_secret": "your-app-secret",
      "token": "callback-token",
      "aes_key": "callback-aes-key",
      "agent_id": "your-agent-id"
    }
  }
}
```

## Feishu Configuration

```json
{
  "channel": {
    "feishu": {
      "enabled": true,
      "app_id": "your-app-id",
      "app_secret": "your-app-secret",
      "verification_token": "your-verification-token",
      "encrypt_key": "your-encrypt-key"
    }
  }
}
```

## WeCom Configuration

```json
{
  "channel": {
    "wecom": {
      "enabled": true,
      "corp_id": "your-corp-id",
      "agent_id": "your-agent-id",
      "secret": "your-secret",
      "token": "callback-token",
      "encoding_aes_key": "your-encoding-aes-key"
    }
  }
}
```

## Personal WeChat Protocols

| Protocol | Features | Key Config |
|----------|----------|------------|
| `openwechat` | Web protocol, free | Set `uos: true` for desktop mode |
| `gewechat` | iPad protocol, stable | Paid service, set HTTP API URL |
| `wcferry` | PC Hook, full features | Requires Windows PC with injector |
| `wechaty` | gRPC bridge | Requires Puppet Token |

> ⚠️ Personal WeChat integration uses unofficial protocols with account ban risks. Use a test account, not your primary one.

websocket.detail:
## Establish Connection

```javascript
const ws = new WebSocket('ws://localhost:8080/api/v1/ws');

ws.onopen = () => {
  console.log('WebSocket connected');
};

ws.onmessage = (event) => {
  const data = JSON.parse(event.data);
  console.log('Received:', data);
};
```

## Message Types

| Type | Description | Example |
|------|-------------|----------|
| `stream` | Streaming response | Agent outputs reply token by token |
| `state_change` | State change | thinking → tool_calling → completed |
| `hitl_request` | Approval request | Agent needs to perform dangerous operation |
| `notification` | Notification | Real-time message alerts |

## Message Format

```json
{
  "type": "stream",
  "session_id": "sess-abc123",
  "data": {
    "content": "Analyzing",
    "done": false
  }
}
```

```json
{
  "type": "state_change",
  "session_id": "sess-abc123",
  "data": {
    "state": "tool_calling",
    "tool": "read_file",
    "args": {"path": "main.go"}
  }
}
```

## Configuration

WebSocket must be enabled in config:

```json
{
  "hitl": {
    "websocket_enabled": true
  }
}
```

> The frontend WebSocket client has built-in **auto-reconnect** on disconnect. The Gateway also provides a WebSocket RPC endpoint at `/api/v1/rpc/ws` with Bearer token auth.
